<% content_for :title, "PostgreSQL Instructions — AACT" %>

<div class="mb-6">
  <%= render "shared/back_link", path: snapshots_path, label: "Snapshots" %>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">PostgreSQL Database Instructions</h1>
</div>

<div class="max-w-3xl space-y-8">
  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
      The PostgreSQL snapshots contain complete dumps of the AACT database that can be loaded into your local
      PostgreSQL installation. This option is ideal for users who need complex queries, best performance, or
      integration with other databases and tools.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
      The AACT system provides access to the <strong>30 most recent daily snapshots</strong> along with
      permanent <strong>monthly archives</strong> created on the first day of each month.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Prerequisites</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>PostgreSQL:</strong> Version 14 or higher recommended. Download from
        <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/download/" class="text-blue hover:underline" target="_blank">postgresql.org</a>.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Disk Space:</strong> At least 10 GB available.</li>
      <li><strong>RAM:</strong> 8 GB or more recommended for optimal restore performance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-6">Steps</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-6">
      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Download a snapshot</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            Get the <%= link_to "latest snapshot", snapshots_path, class: "text-blue hover:underline" %> or
            browse the <%= link_to "archive", archive_snapshots_path(type: "pgdump"), class: "text-blue hover:underline" %> for older data.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Extract the ZIP file</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            Extract the downloaded ZIP file. The key file inside is <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">postgres.dmp</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Create a local database</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 bg-gray-900 text-green-400 text-sm rounded-md px-4 py-3 font-mono">
            createdb aact
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Restore from the dump file</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 bg-gray-900 text-green-400 text-sm rounded-md px-4 py-3 font-mono">
            pg_restore -e -v -O -x -d aact --no-owner path/to/postgres.dmp
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            To replace an existing AACT database, add <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">--clean</code> to the command.
            Restore typically takes 5–15 minutes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">5</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Connect and query</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 bg-gray-900 text-green-400 text-sm rounded-md px-4 py-3 font-mono">
            psql -d aact
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            Verify the restore with: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">SELECT count(*) FROM studies;</code>
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Troubleshooting</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Permission errors:</strong> Run commands with your PostgreSQL superuser or check role privileges.</li>
      <li><strong>Database already exists:</strong> Use <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">dropdb aact</code> first, or add <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">--clean</code> to pg_restore.</li>
      <li><strong>Out of disk space:</strong> Ensure at least 10 GB free before restoring.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
